{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report", "label": "Validation Report (P10-11, the trial)", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The third volume: nothing decided, everything measured \u2014 Phase 10 races the frozen object vs fair ER (S14), Phase 11 draws the LIMIT-MAP on real data + scale (S15)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_experience_replay", "label": "Experience Replay (ER) \u2014 the fair budgeted baseline", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The steel-manned opponent: under a matched FLOPs/sample + memory-bytes budget a well-tuned ER beats the fancy CL methods (Prabhu/Ghunaim). Byte-matched to OURS's LUT, tuned on a disjoint seed, re-tuned per arena in P11."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_pareto_verdict", "label": "The Pareto verdict (P10.6)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "On (accuracy x energy) a small tuned ER dominates OURS(grid-4); OURS's genuine wins live off that axis \u2014 worst-case continual safety, noise robustness, the substrate floor."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_s14", "label": "S14 (Phase 10 close-out decision)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A substrate-native continual learner: ties ER on the continual home, trails static digits, WINS continual safety ~10x + noise on every channel; energy edge substrate-realized (1.5x more same-substrate algorithm, chip 3.4x cheaper). Founding bet refined not inflated."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_s15", "label": "S15 (Phase 11 limit map decision)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The LIMIT-MAP: 8 arenas x 5 channels; WINS real gas sensor drift + order-invariance + every scaling read (substrate factor grows 5.4->7.4x, C=20 retention crossover); FLOORS autocorrelated streams; static accuracy trails; losses/floors shipped."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_founding_bet", "label": "The founding bet (economics AND accuracy vs backprop)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "'An 80/20 forward-only continual learner that beats backprop's economics AND accuracy.' Banked as two halves: economics substrate-realized (the chip, not the algorithm); accuracy = continual stability, not static."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_cadence_frontier", "label": "Cadence cost-frontier family (grid-4 the headline)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The frozen object shown as operating points along its one runtime dial \u2014 the sleep cadence (grid-N = sleep every N segments). grid-4 committed, never swapped; the Tier-2 break is a plateau + two localized cliffs (safety plunge 6->7, accuracy cliff 15->16)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_substrate_realized_energy", "label": "Substrate-realized energy (the analog crossbar floor)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The load-bearing energy cut is same-substrate E(OURS-digital) vs E(ER-digital) \u2014 there OURS's deep bulk is ~1.5x MORE. The chip win is the analog compute-in-memory crossbar (a meter-structural floor that grows 5.4->7.4x with width), never the contestable claim. Behavioral meter, not SPICE."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_gauntlet", "label": "The multi-domain gauntlet (the money figure)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "5 native domain-IL digit worlds (identity/permuted/rotated/covariate/noised). OURS rides flat; ER saw-tooths at every switch. Reversed order: ER collapses (0.343 vs 0.504), OURS order-invariant. Retention win is switch-frequency-scoped (E8 alignment-break)."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_limit_map", "label": "The LIMIT-MAP (P11.9 deliverable)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "8 arenas x 5 capability channels, every cell win/tie/loss/FLOOR with its number; the Delta-bulk overlay keys it to mechanism (bulk = nonlinear learner where data is nonlinear; safety = namer+gate+sleep). Grey is honesty, not defeat."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_gas_stream", "label": "Gas sensor drift stream (the real-world headline win)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Nature's own coherent covariate drift (sensor aging): OURS prequential 0.789 >= a per-arena-tuned ER 0.756, +0.184 over persistence; Arm B 0.856. The frozen recipe is the strongest online learner where the drift is a genuine covariate shift."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_prabhu_er", "label": "Prabhu CVPR'23 (budgeted ER is strong)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Under a matched FLOPs/sample+bytes budget a well-tuned ER beats fancy CL methods \u2014 the reason the trial's honest opponent is a budgeted tuned ER."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_ghunaim", "label": "Ghunaim CVPR'23 (real-time / online CL budget)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The real-time throughput/steps-behind read cashed into the money figure."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_validation_report_souza2020", "label": "Souza 2020 (label-autocorrelated stream trap)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The ELEC2 persistence trap: on HAR/electricity/covertype no learner beats 'predict the previous label' \u2014 a known property of those streams, why P11 floors honestly there."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft6_0_src_validation_report", "target": "draft6_0_src_stage1_report", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_src_validation_report", "target": "draft6_0_src_stage2_report", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\src\\validation-report.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_src_validation_report", "target": "draft6_0_src_phase10_phase10_report", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "dra